\begin{proof}
        Let $h\in G_{(\ast,\star)}^{X^2\setminus\Delta}$ and let $V$ be a neighbourhood of $x$. It is enough to consider in place of $V$ a basic product neighbourhood: $v\in V$ if and only if $h_x\in V_x$ for all $x$ belonging to a finite set $F\subseteq X$, where each $V_x$ is a neighbourhood of $h_x$ in $G_{(\ast,\star)}$. The open subgroup $O=\cap_{x\in F}{\mbox{\rm St}}_x$ of $G$ has the property $O\cdot V=V$.
